fields.name: CHROM
fields.label: CHROM
fields.description: Chromosome identifier

fields.name: POS
fields.label: POS
fields.description: The reference position

fields.name: ID
fields.label: ID
fields.description: Semi-colon separated list of unique identifiers where available

fields.name: REF
fields.label: REF
fields.description: The value in the POS field refers to the position of the first base in the String

fields.name: ALT
fields.label: ALT
fields.description: Comma separated list of alternate non-reference alleles called on at least one of the samples

fields.name: QUAL
fields.label: QUAL
fields.description: Quality

fields.name: FILTER
fields.label: FILTER
fields.description: Filter status

fields.name: INFO_RS
fields.label: INFO_RS
fields.description: dbSNP ID (i.e. rs number)

fields.name: INFO_RSPOS
fields.label: INFO_RSPOS
fields.description: Chr position reported in dbSNP

fields.name: INFO_RV
fields.label: INFO_RV
fields.description: RS orientation is reversed

fields.name: INFO_VP
fields.label: INFO_VP
fields.description: Variation Property.  Documentation is at ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/snp/specs/dbSNP_BitField_latest.pdf

fields.name: INFO_GENEINFO
fields.label: INFO_GENEINFO
fields.description: Pairs each of gene symbol:gene id.  The gene symbol and id are delimited by a colon (:) and each pair is delimited by a vertical bar (|)

fields.name: INFO_dbSNPBuildID
fields.label: INFO_dbSNPBuildID
fields.description: First dbSNP Build for RS

fields.name: INFO_SAO
fields.label: INFO_SAO
fields.description: Variant Allele Origin: 0 - unspecified, 1 - Germline, 2 - Somatic, 3 - Both

fields.name: INFO_SSR
fields.label: INFO_SSR
fields.description: Variant Suspect Reason Codes (may be more than one value added together) 0 - unspecified, 1 - Paralog, 2 - byEST, 4 - oldAlign, 8 - Para_EST, 16 - 1kg_failed, 1024 - other

fields.name: INFO_WGT
fields.label: INFO_WGT
fields.description: Weight, 00 - unmapped, 1 - weight 1, 2 - weight 2, 3 - weight 3 or more

fields.name: INFO_VC
fields.label: INFO_VC
fields.description: Variation Class

fields.name: INFO_PM
fields.label: INFO_PM
fields.description: Variant is Precious(Clinical,Pubmed Cited)

fields.name: INFO_TPA
fields.label: INFO_TPA
fields.description: Provisional Third Party Annotation(TPA) (currently rs from PHARMGKB who will give phenotype data)

fields.name: INFO_PMC
fields.label: INFO_PMC
fields.description: Links exist to PubMed Central article

fields.name: INFO_S3D
fields.label: INFO_S3D
fields.description: Has 3D structure - SNP3D table

fields.name: INFO_SLO
fields.label: INFO_SLO
fields.description: Has SubmitterLinkOut - From SNP->SubSNP->Batch.link_out

fields.name: INFO_NSF
fields.label: INFO_NSF
fields.description: Has non-synonymous frameshift A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes all downstream amino acids. FxnClass = 44

fields.name: INFO_NSM
fields.label: INFO_NSM
fields.description: Has non-synonymous missense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes protein peptide. FxnClass = 42

fields.name: INFO_NSN
fields.label: INFO_NSN
fields.description: Has non-synonymous nonsense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes to STOP codon (TER). FxnClass = 41

fields.name: INFO_REF
fields.label: INFO_REF
fields.description: Has reference A coding region variation where one allele in the set is identical to the reference sequence. FxnCode = 8

fields.name: INFO_SYN
fields.label: INFO_SYN
fields.description: Has synonymous A coding region variation where one allele in the set does not change the encoded amino acid. FxnCode = 3

fields.name: INFO_U3
fields.label: INFO_U3
fields.description: In 3' UTR Location is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCode = 53

fields.name: INFO_U5
fields.label: INFO_U5
fields.description: In 5' UTR Location is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCode = 55

fields.name: INFO_ASS
fields.label: INFO_ASS
fields.description: In acceptor splice site FxnCode = 73

fields.name: INFO_DSS
fields.label: INFO_DSS
fields.description: In donor splice-site FxnCode = 75

fields.name: INFO_INT
fields.label: INFO_INT
fields.description: In Intron FxnCode = 6

fields.name: INFO_R3
fields.label: INFO_R3
fields.description: In 3' gene region FxnCode = 13

fields.name: INFO_R5
fields.label: INFO_R5
fields.description: In 5' gene region FxnCode = 15

fields.name: INFO_OTH
fields.label: INFO_OTH
fields.description: Has other variant with exactly the same set of mapped positions on NCBI refernce assembly.

fields.name: INFO_CFL
fields.label: INFO_CFL
fields.description: Has Assembly conflict. This is for weight 1 and 2 variant that maps to different chromosomes on different assemblies.

fields.name: INFO_ASP
fields.label: INFO_ASP
fields.description: Is Assembly specific. This is set if the variant only maps to one assembly

fields.name: INFO_MUT
fields.label: INFO_MUT
fields.description: Is mutation (journal citation, explicit fact): a low frequency variation that is cited in journal and other reputable sources

fields.name: INFO_VLD
fields.label: INFO_VLD
fields.description: Is Validated.  This bit is set if the variant has 2+ minor allele count based on frequency or genotype data.

fields.name: INFO_G5A
fields.label: INFO_G5A
fields.description: >5% minor allele frequency in each and all populations

fields.name: INFO_G5
fields.label: INFO_G5
fields.description: >5% minor allele frequency in 1+ populations

fields.name: INFO_HD
fields.label: INFO_HD
fields.description: Marker is on high density genotyping kit (50K density or greater).  The variant may have phenotype associations present in dbGaP.

fields.name: INFO_GNO
fields.label: INFO_GNO
fields.description: Genotypes available. The variant has individual genotype (in SubInd table).

fields.name: INFO_KGPhase1
fields.label: INFO_KGPhase1
fields.description: 1000 Genome phase 1 (incl. June Interim phase 1)

fields.name: INFO_KGPhase3
fields.label: INFO_KGPhase3
fields.description: 1000 Genome phase 3

fields.name: INFO_CDA
fields.label: INFO_CDA
fields.description: Variation is interrogated in a clinical diagnostic assay

fields.name: INFO_LSD
fields.label: INFO_LSD
fields.description: Submitted from a locus-specific database

fields.name: INFO_MTP
fields.label: INFO_MTP
fields.description: Microattribution/third-party annotation(TPA:GWAS,PAGE)

fields.name: INFO_OM
fields.label: INFO_OM
fields.description: Has OMIM/OMIA

fields.name: INFO_NOC
fields.label: INFO_NOC
fields.description: Contig allele not present in variant allele list. The reference sequence allele at the mapped position is not present in the variant allele list, adjusted for orientation.

fields.name: INFO_WTD
fields.label: INFO_WTD
fields.description: Is Withdrawn by submitter If one member ss is withdrawn by submitter, then this bit is set.  If all member ss' are withdrawn, then the rs is deleted to SNPHistory

fields.name: INFO_NOV
fields.label: INFO_NOV
fields.description: Rs cluster has non-overlapping allele sets. True when rs set has more than 2 alleles from different submissions and these sets share no alleles in common.

fields.name: INFO_CAF
fields.label: INFO_CAF
fields.description: An ordered, comma delimited list of allele frequencies based on 1000Genomes, starting with the reference allele followed by alternate alleles as ordered in the ALT column. Where a 1000Genomes alternate allele is not in the dbSNPs alternate allele set, the allele is added to the ALT column.  The minor allele is the second largest value in the list, and was previuosly reported in VCF as the GMAF.  This is the GMAF reported on the RefSNP and EntrezSNP pages and VariationReporter

fields.name: INFO_COMMON
fields.label: INFO_COMMON
fields.description: RS is a common SNP.  A common SNP is one that has at least one 1000Genomes population with a minor allele of frequency >= 1% and for which 2 or more founders contribute to that minor allele frequency.
